video.title: Chicago Med
video.synopsis: The doctors and nurses of Gaffney Chicago Medical Center juggle the busy ER's dramas and dangers in this spinoff of "Chicago Fire" and "Chicago P.D."

episodes.synopsis: The ER's grand opening is interrupted by an onslaught of crash victims, pushing hospital administrator Sharon Goodwin and her staff to their limits.
episodes.title: Derailed

episodes.synopsis: As Dr. Choi treats a bleeding teenage girl, he discovers she's just given birth, sparking a frantic search for her abandoned baby.
episodes.title: iNO

episodes.synopsis: When Dr. Rhodes takes the case of a family friend who's been impaled by glass shards, he's reunited with his sister and forced to confront his past.
episodes.title: Fallback

episodes.synopsis: After shots ring out at a movie theater, the doctors work to treat the victims while Goodwin attempts to keep the press at bay.
episodes.title: Mistaken

episodes.synopsis: Following a knife attack, a member of the team takes a sudden turn for the worse, leaving Dr. Rhodes and Dr. Zanetti racing against the clock.
episodes.title: Malignant

episodes.synopsis: After two airplane stowaways are brought into the hospital with major injuries, Goodwin gets a visit from the Department of Homeland Security.
episodes.title: Bound

episodes.synopsis: When legal issues stall a lifesaving bone marrow transplant, Goodwin weighs whether to disobey direct orders or put a patient's life in jeopardy.
episodes.title: Saints

episodes.synopsis: Dr. Manning returns from maternity leave and helps treat a teen with a long history of medical issues. Dr. Choi attends to a former Navy shipmate.
episodes.title: Reunion

episodes.synopsis: Dr. Halstead revives a patient with cancer who has a do-not-resuscitate order, prompting a lawsuit against Chicago Med.
episodes.title: Choices

episodes.synopsis: A new set of lungs could save a patient's life through an innovative surgical procedure, but an unforeseen medical problem arises.
episodes.title: Clarity

episodes.synopsis: Dr. Rhodes and Dr. Choi disagree over the final decision made by a patient suffering from a life-threatening heart condition.
episodes.title: Intervention

episodes.synopsis: Nurse Lockwood gets arrested for refusing to violate hospital policy and draw blood without consent from a patient suspected of a DUI.
episodes.title: Guilty

episodes.synopsis: Goodwin and Dr. Halstead deal with a man intent on harvesting his recently deceased wife's eggs but soon discover surprising information.
episodes.title: Us

episodes.synopsis: An erratic patient comes to the emergency department claiming that his heart is pounding inside his head and takes drastic measures to stop it.
episodes.title: Hearts

episodes.synopsis: Dr. Manning and Dr. Charles deal with a 16-year-old patient suffering from abdominal pain who refuses any drugs for fear of winding up addicted.
episodes.title: Inheritance

episodes.synopsis: When Dr. Rhodes and Dr. Downey treat a patient with a multitude of health issues, they realize he might have been misdiagnosed.
episodes.title: Disorder

episodes.synopsis: April and Dr. Halstead see a homeless man with alcoholism suffering from a broken leg, but they don't agree about the best course of treatment.
episodes.title: Withdrawal

episodes.synopsis: Dr. Rhodes tends to Dr. Downey while Goodwin is forced to deal with personal issues. April encounters a disorderly patient.
episodes.title: Timing

episodes.synopsis: Dr. Rhodes begins his fellowship in cardiothoracic surgery but gets off on the wrong foot with his challenging new boss, Dr. Latham.
episodes.title: Soul Care

episodes.synopsis: Dr. Manning and Dr. Rhodes separately treat complicated cases involving sick babies, only to uncover that the two cases could actually be intertwined.
episodes.title: Win Loss

episodes.synopsis: Dr. Manning and med student Jeff Clarke must figure out a mystery illness when a man who doesn't speak English arrives at the hospital in dire straits.
episodes.title: Natural History

episodes.synopsis: When several patients are diagnosed with the same rare infection, Dr. Charles' daughter, an epidemiologist, is brought in to find the common link.
episodes.title: Brother's Keeper

episodes.synopsis: A car accident at the Chicago Marathon forces Dr. Halstead, April and her medical resident brother to perform a difficult procedure in the field.
episodes.title: Extreme Measures

episodes.synopsis: Dr. Manning tends to a young woman with cancer and struggles to tell her parents about the seriousness of her condition.
episodes.title: Alternative Medicine

episodes.synopsis: Goodwin's childhood sweetheart arrives at the hospital. To help get his financial footing, Dr. Halstead gets lured into a concierge doctor app idea.
episodes.title: Inherent Bias

episodes.synopsis: Dr. Halstead and Dr. Manning deal with two warring brothers who are brought together when one finds himself in desperate need of a kidney.
episodes.title: Free Will

episodes.synopsis: Goodwin tasks Dr. Charles with evaluating a patient as a possible heart recipient, while Jeff makes a confession to Dr. Manning.
episodes.title: Uncharted Territory

episodes.synopsis: Dr. Rhodes and Dr. Charles' heart transplant patient gets into a car crash, revealing issues that could complicate her surgery.
episodes.title: Heart Matters

episodes.synopsis: It's a long night on the graveyard shift  especially for Dr. Reese, who must deal with pronouncing patients dead on more than one occasion.
episodes.title: Graveyard Shift

episodes.synopsis: Dr. Manning and Dr. Charles treat a teenage girl with a rapidly changing set of symptoms that has everyone perplexed.
episodes.title: Mirror Mirror

episodes.synopsis: Dr. Rhodes convinces Dr. Latham to join him for a medical trip out of town, putting Latham's personality issues to the test.
episodes.title: Theseus' Ship

episodes.synopsis: The doctors and nurses of Chicago Med brace for an influx of trauma patients when a pre-dawn pileup finds the hospital in full scramble mode.
episodes.title: Cold Front

episodes.synopsis: A teen in a psychiatric facility contacts Dr. Reese, and Dr. Manning tries to help parents make a decision about their comatose daughter's pregnancy.
episodes.title: Lose Yourself

episodes.synopsis: It's a miracle when a trauma patient survives the trip to the hospital, putting the pressure on Dr. Rhodes to keep the man alive.
episodes.title: Prisoner's Dilemma

episodes.synopsis: Dr. Choi and Dr. Halstead butt heads over how to treat a patient with stroke symptoms, while Dr. Manning treats a young boy who fell in the river.
episodes.title: Monday Mourning

episodes.synopsis: Will grapples with a moral decision when his former teacher, Dr. Bella Rowan, is faced with a life-threatening disease.
episodes.title: Lesson Learned

episodes.synopsis: A hacker demanding a ransom payment shuts down the hospital computer system, forcing the doctors to diagnose patients without the aid of technology.
episodes.title: Ctrl Alt

episodes.synopsis: Things get personal for Dr. Halstead when his unsupportive father is admitted to the hospital against his wishes.
episodes.title: Generation Gap

episodes.synopsis: Dr. Rhodes fights to save a woman who's desperate to help her daughter survive cancer. Dr. Charles asks Sarah to conduct his daughter's psych evaluation.
episodes.title: Deliver Us

episodes.synopsis: Dr. Rhodes challenges Dr. Charles and other hospital staff over the proper treatment for Robin. Dr. Manning seeks help from Detective Halstead.
episodes.title: White Butterflies

episodes.synopsis: A new hotshot doctor arrives at Chicago Med, creating competition for Dr. Rhodes. Dr. Halstead and Dr. Manning work together to diagnose a refugee.
episodes.title: Love Hurts

episodes.synopsis: The doctors of Chicago Med take their opinions to the extreme as they try to bring justice to the perpetrator of a shooting.
episodes.title: Speak Your Truth

episodes.synopsis: Dr. Manning goes to great lengths to help a frightened pregnant woman whose baby is severely underdeveloped.
episodes.title: Nothing to Fear

episodes.synopsis: When Goodwin receives financial complaints from the hospital board, she's forced to implement new guidelines that cause headaches for the doctors.
episodes.title: Trust Your Gut

episodes.synopsis: Dr. Charles learns a troubling fact about the man who shot him. Dr. Rhodes and Dr. Bekker come to an agreement during a complicated surgery.
episodes.title: Naughty Or Nice

episodes.synopsis: When a young woman with no insurance refuses to take an HIV test, Goodwin and Dr. Choi attempt to treat her without draining the hospital's resources.
episodes.title: Mountains and Molehills

episodes.synopsis: Dr. Choi attempts to diagnose a man with no symptoms while Dr. Reese's paranoia goes to the extreme when she uses pepper spray on an aggressive patient.
episodes.title: Ties that Bind

episodes.synopsis: Dr. Charles feels pressure when Dr. Choi and Dr. Manning criticize his medical decision regarding a sick newborn baby.
episodes.title: Over Troubled Water

episodes.synopsis: Dr. Choi struggles to help a woman cope with anorexia. After a two-week suspension, Dr. Reese is immediately put to the test by Dr. Charles.
episodes.title: Lemons and Lemonade

episodes.synopsis: After discovering that a patient's family might have been abusive, Dr. Choi and April contemplate calling child services.
episodes.title: On Shaky Ground

episodes.synopsis: After witnessing a drive-by shooting and hitting her head, Dr. Manning struggles with the aftermath of the resulting injury.
episodes.title: Down by Law

episodes.synopsis: Dr. Choi enlists April's help when a neighbor is stabbed. Dr. Bekker and Dr. Rhodes' expertise is put to the test when Noah misdiagnoses a patient.
episodes.title: Folie  Deux

episodes.synopsis: Dr. Manning and Dr. Choi deliver a baby under dire circumstances. Dr. Rhodes and Dr. Bekker debate the best way to treat a boy with a chronic disease.
episodes.title: Born This Way

episodes.synopsis: When a mother makes a decision regarding care of her adult son, Dr. Halstead and Dr. Manning find themselves at odds.
episodes.title: Best Laid Plans

episodes.synopsis: After a baby is abducted from Med, Goodwin enlists the help of Dr. Charles and Dr. Reese to find the suspect, and the hospital goes into lockdown.
episodes.title: Lock It Down

episodes.synopsis: Dr. Charles and Dr. Reese search for answers when a mother claims her daughter is possessed. Dr. Rhodes and Dr. Bekker try to save conjoined twins.
episodes.title: Devil in Disguise

episodes.synopsis: After taking the lead on a surgery, Dr. Bekker feels the heat when something goes wrong. April and Dr. Reese rush to find the son of a dying patient.
episodes.title: An Inconvenient Truth

episodes.synopsis: When a 10-year-old boy is admitted to the hospital, Dr. Manning and Dr. Halstead disagree about how to best handle his parents.
episodes.title: The Parent Trap

episodes.synopsis: After a shooting occurs during a block party at a local park, Med is overrun with victims that stretch the hospital and staff to its limits.
episodes.title: This is Now

episodes.synopsis: Dr. Manning rushes to save a young boy who has a life-threatening case of the flu. April believes Dr. Choi's sister stole opioid painkillers.
episodes.title: Crisis of Confidence

episodes.synopsis: Dr. Rhodes second-guesses his decision to remove himself from the team of doctors working to separate conjoined twins.
episodes.title: The Tipping Point

episodes.synopsis: Goodwin quickly finds herself clashing with new hospital COO Gwen Garrett while April questions whether Dr. Choi's sister, Emily, is using again.
episodes.title: Be My Better Half

episodes.synopsis: The doctors and nurses find themselves on high alert when Chicago Med overflows with patients in the wake of a terrifying fire at an apartment complex.
episodes.title: When to Let Go

episodes.synopsis: When a sick boy is brought in, Dr. Choi is faced with a tough decision that quickly escalates into a complicated and dangerous situation.
episodes.title: Heavy is the Head

episodes.synopsis: Dr. Halstead gets an unexpected visit from the CPD, while Dr. Choi is skeptical of a woman who's experiencing chronic pain.
episodes.title: Backed Against the Wall

episodes.synopsis: When things get complicated, Dr. Halstead is forced to lie to Dr. Manning. Dr. Choi and April learn compromising information about Emily's boyfriend.
episodes.title: What You Don't Know

episodes.synopsis: Dr. Manning and Dr. Halstead become skeptical about a patient's injuries when the victim of a car accident is brought into the hospital.
episodes.title: Lesser of Two Evils

episodes.synopsis: The hospital is forced to evacuate when a toxic chemical puts the staff and patients in grave danger. Dr. Charles and Dr. Manning take drastic measures.
episodes.title: The Poison Inside Us

episodes.synopsis: Dr. Charles struggles to convince Dr. Choi that surgery isn't always the answer. Dr. Rhodes finds himself in hot water with Goodwin.
episodes.title: Play By My Rules

episodes.synopsis: Dr. Halstead and Dr. Manning prepare for their big day, but an unsuspecting Will soon finds himself sidetracked.
episodes.title: Death Do Us Part

episodes.synopsis: April finds herself in a dangerous situation, and Dr. Manning gets an update on Dr. Halstead. Dr. Rhodes gears up for a gala honoring his hybrid OR.
episodes.title: All the Lonely People

episodes.synopsis: Dr. Halstead adjusts to hospital life in the aftermath of his undercover activities. Dr. Choi and April's relationship starts to interfere with work.
episodes.title: Who Can You Trust

episodes.synopsis: Dr. Halstead rushes to rescue Dr. Manning when she's involved in a helicopter crash. The personal drama between Dr. Rhodes and Dr. Bekker boils over.
episodes.title: The Things We Do

episodes.synopsis: Dr. Halstead withholds some important information from Dr. Manning, and she begins to question his suspicious behavior.
episodes.title: Ghosts in the Attic

episodes.synopsis: Dr. Halstead's personal issues continue to interfere with his relationship with Dr. Manning and his life at the hospital.
episodes.title: Can't Unring That Bell

episodes.synopsis: After witnessing a pickup truck plow through a street fair, Dr. Manning and Maggie are forced to make some tough decisions on the fly.
episodes.title: We Hold These Truths

episodes.synopsis: Dr. Manning and Dr. Halstead grow further apart. Dr. Charles struggles to come to terms with his feelings toward his ex-wife.
episodes.title: Old Flames, New Sparks

episodes.synopsis: When a car smashes through the ambulance bay doors, Dr. Choi faces difficult decisions in order to save a trapped worker and help April.
episodes.title: The Space Between Us

episodes.synopsis: Dr. Rhodes receives an alarming phone call that prompts him to rush out in the middle of an important surgery. Dr. Halstead aids an FBI agent.
episodes.title: Tell Me the Truth

episodes.synopsis: The hospital goes into lockdown mode when a man with a gun holds medical staff hostage. Goodwin is forced to make a tough decision.
episodes.title: Never Let You Go

episodes.synopsis: Dr. Charles and Dr. Manning disagree about how to handle a patient who's poisoning herself. Dr. Rhodes makes serious accusations about Dr. Bekker.
episodes.title: More Harm Than Good

episodes.synopsis: Caroline has news to share, forcing Dr. Charles to make a decision about their relationship. Maggie meets her sister's new boyfriend.
episodes.title: Forever Hold Your Peace

episodes.synopsis: Dr. Charles and Caroline make some major plans. Dr. Bekker fights to keep her relationship with Dr. Rhodes. Agent Lee gives Dr. Halstead alarming news.
episodes.title: With a Brave Heart

episodes.synopsis: Chicago Med deals with the aftermath of a horrific car accident, and an investigation is launched following a suspicious death.
episodes.title: Never Going Back to Normal

episodes.synopsis: A power outage at Med puts multiple patients at risk and tests the skills of the staff and their enthusiastic med students.
episodes.title: We're Lost in the Dark

episodes.synopsis: Dr. Choi and Dr. Charles have difficult decisions to make as a dying man tries to preserve his future life with a controversial scientific method.
episodes.title: In the Valley of the Shadows

episodes.synopsis: An apartment complex is forced into quarantine when cases of a deadly virus turn into an epidemic. CPD chases a lead that could point to bioterrorism.
episodes.title: Infection, Pt. 2

episodes.synopsis: Dr. Choi and Dr. Marcel don't see eye to eye over the treatment of a patient's chronic pain. Rumors start to circulate about Maggie.
episodes.title: Got a Friend in Me

episodes.synopsis: Dr. Manning's actions with a recent patient lead to serious repercussions. Dr. Charles is visited by a childhood friend with a surprising revelation.
episodes.title: It's All in the Family

episodes.synopsis: Dr. Charles and Dr. Halstead sink their teeth into a bloodthirsty case. Dr. Marcel and Maggie throw a traditional crawfish boil for the staff.
episodes.title: Who Knows What Tomorrow Brings

episodes.synopsis: Maggie gets unsettling news about a new friend and breaks protocol to support him. A social media influencer lets his users vote on medical advice.
episodes.title: Too Close to the Sun

episodes.synopsis: April receives unfortunate news that makes her question her future with Dr. Choi. Dr. Charles and Maggie see tough times on the horizon.
episodes.title: I Can't Imagine the Future

episodes.synopsis: Dr. Halstead's world is thrown into turmoil when a former patient resurfaces. April has a secret she considers confessing to Dr. Choi.
episodes.title: Guess It Doesn't Matter Anymore

episodes.synopsis: After an accident at O'Hare, one of the ED's own may be in danger. Dr. Halstead's proposal for a safe injection site goes to the board.
episodes.title: The Ground Shifts Beneath Us

episodes.synopsis: The team deals with the aftermath of a school bus crash. Dr. Charles worries Dr. Halstead is putting his medical license in jeopardy.
episodes.title: Leave the Choice to Solomon

episodes.synopsis: Two brothers in critical condition are rushed to the hospital by their parents, leaving Dr. Choi, April and Dr. Charles to tend to their care.
episodes.title: Pain Is for the Living

episodes.synopsis: Dr. Manning and Dr. Marcel disagree over an abusive husband. Dr. Halstead struggles with ethics and his decision to work at the safe injection site.
episodes.title: It May Not Be Forever

episodes.synopsis: Dr. Charles and Dr. Manning treat a patient who's fully invested in pretending to be someone other than himself. Dr. Sexton begins to doubt himself.
episodes.title: I Will Do No Harm

episodes.synopsis: A convicted murderer's escape hits close to home when several members of the team find themselves in danger. Maggie finally receives some good news.
episodes.title: Who Should Be the Judge

episodes.synopsis: Dr. Manning and Dr. Charles assist in a complicated case involving a 4-year-old. Relationships are put to the test as secrets are revealed.
episodes.title: The Ghosts of the Past

episodes.synopsis: Dr. Charles and Goodwin fear Dr. Halstead is repeating his past mistakes when a patient with early-onset Alzheimer's is brought into the ED.
episodes.title: In the Name of Love

episodes.synopsis: Dr. Charles evaluates a 15-year-old who's brought into the ED after an apparent fall. Dr. Halstead sides with Dr. Asher on a risky treatment plan.
episodes.title: Just a River in Egypt

episodes.synopsis: Dr. Marcel is visited by two New Orleans detectives who have questions about his past. Dr. Choi puts his life in danger to save a child.
episodes.title: A Needle in the Heart
